I have recently been giving Claude Code a thorough road-test. I've been very demanding in my requests, I asked for Stripe Credit Card payments, Azure Storage to save files, an Azure Cosmos Database for high availability and scalability, QR Code generation, Microsoft, Google and local account registration and login, and very specific processes for how to structure outputs.

In this blog post, I will outline the good and the bad and give my honest opinion on Claude Code as it stands today.

---

## What is Claude Code and How does it work? 

Put simply, Claude Code in an extension that you can install into a code IDE (Integrated Development Environment) such as Visual Studios Code, in my case and as long as you pay for Claude professional or above, you tell Claude Code what you want to achieve and it will go through your code and make the neccessary changes. 

Sounds cool right? This must be the end of Software Engineers! Not at all, from my experiences, I would describe Claude Code as being like a very energetic puppy; it'll try to do things quickly but it'll make a lot of mistakes and mess along the way. So let's explore what went well and what did go well at all.

## What went well?

What impresses the most about Claude Code is it's very fast. No Software Engineer can read all the code files, make a list of jobs to complete and add or delete code within a few minutes. Even with the assistance of GitHub Co-pilot to suggest the code we would like to write, we wouldn't be able to develop at this pace.

I have already documented that Claude produces some stunning UIs(User Interfaces) in this blog post: [Challenge: Build an Insurance Policy Admin System in 2 Days Using AI](_posts/2026-03-25-InsurancePASin2Days.md). 

## What didn't go well?

Unfortunately, many things did not go well during my thorough road test:

- **The lies** - I posed a question to Claude code, about if it was neccessary to provide one user with a reference number to give to another, when the next user cannot search for the reference number or use it whatsoever. I was confidently told the reference number was very important and it was used inside my application. When I confronted Claude Code with evidence of it's lies, it told me it was sorry and overconfident, that it didn't even check the programming code, that I was correct to flag this and that it had fixed the issue.

- **Spending you're usage quota fixing problems it created itself** - This is a very common frustration. Even with a professional subscription, you're still restricted to a quota and Claude Code will burn through the quota quickly to fix issues it created within the code. If your quota runs out, it will halt fixing issues, until your quota is refreshed and sometimes the refresh will not happen for another 3 hours.

- **Not Cleaning-Up After Itself** - On a few occasions Claude code will identify a bug as some code that it had previous rewritten but not deleted. Just yesterday, when I asked why a feature was not working, it said it was because I was writing code to a local database. That same morning I had asked that we migrate out of a local database and into an Azure cloud database. Claude code sometimes writes new code but leaves the old code behind. Another example was when I asked for a full code review and Claude code found left-over pieces of code that were no longer referenced.

- **Bad Technology Advice** -  I made it clear to Claude code from the beginning that my long-term goal was to use Azure Cosmos Database with a C# Web API. It suggested that I use SQLite database and an Express API and then migrate later to the cloud. I thought it was odd using a SQL database and later converting to a NoSQL database, but I went along with it for the learning experience. It was a big mistake, because when we did migrate, many original bugs were rewritten in C# and had to be fixed a second time. Also when I confronted Claude Code about this mistake, it said it didn't recall suggesting those technologies and that they were not the right choice considering my long-term goals.

- **Code Quality Issues** - Claude code does not always follow best-practice when it writes code. In C# for example, it tried to fix an issue by changing a type to "Object". An experienced developer would know that this is not the correct syntax choice. If some data is text you might use a "String" datatype, but not an object data-type 

## Final Thoughts

In software engineering we have the development "Golden Triangle" of time vs cost vs quality and we say in every project, we can achieve one of these things at the cost of the others. It could be argued that Claude code achieves speed but at the expense of cost for a professional subscription and even more at the expense of quality.

